global_rules.preamble: You are a meticulous, constraint-aware shift planner.
global_rules.narrative_rules:
Shift Coverage:
Ideally, 3 to 4 employees are assigned to cover the Contact Team starting at 07:00. However, this number may vary due to vacations, sick leave, or other absences.

Pikett Duties:
The employee assigned to Pikett is always responsible for the Contact Team shift starting at 07:00 throughout the week, including Saturday.

08:00 Shift Assignment:
The Contact Team shift starting at 08:00 is staffed only after the requirements for the 07:00 and 09:00 Contact Team shifts are fulfilled.

Weekly Shift Assignment:
Each shift is assigned to an employee for an entire week. Employees assigned to the 07:00 Contact Team shift will cover this shift for the whole week. Exceptions to this rule are rare and typically only occur when multiple employees are on leave and urgent coverage is needed. In such cases, employees assigned to the 08:00 shift may also cover the 09:00 shift if necessary.

Holiday Rules:

24.12: All employees work as usual.
25.12: Only Pikett and Sob Pikett are required to work; all other employees have the day off.
31.12: All employees work as usual.
global_rules.output_format_instructions: Return a valid JSON schedule. Top-level keys: dates[], assignments[], violations[], and notes. Each assignment maps (date, role, shift_id) -> employee_id.

schedule_state.generation_notes:
Scope: This schedule focuses on weekly on-call (Pikett and Pikett SOB) assignments and the associated weekly 07:00 Contact Team coverage by the Pikett assignee for the period 2025-12-08 to 2025-12-31, in line with the rules that the Pikett covers the 07:00 Contact Team shift across the week (incl. Saturday). We honored the 24.12 and 31.12 'as usual' rule and the 25.12 rule (only Pikett and SOB Pikett required; all other employees off) by intentionally not scheduling Contact Team (07:00) on 25.12.
Assignments by week:
- Week 12/08–12/14: Pikett + CT(07:00) = König, Markus-MGB; Pikett SOB = Grusovin, Nico-MGB.
- Week 12/15–12/21: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Bürki, Marcel-MGB; Pikett SOB = Kostadinov, Kostadin-MGB.
- Week 12/22–12/28: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Kupper, Ricardo-MGB (CT not placed on 25.12 per rule); Pikett SOB = Schärer, Roland-MGB.
- 12/29–12/31: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Hajdari, Elmir-MGB. SOB Pikett for 12/29–12/31 is already present in the uploaded plan for Grusovin, Nico-MGB and is therefore not duplicated here.
Fairness/rotation: We avoided assigning the same individual to consecutive multi-weeks of Pikett. We also avoided employees on planned vacations or blockers (e.g., Pivetta, Veiga, Grusovin during their listed holidays) and respected weekday limitations when known.
Conflicts and known limitations:
- Coverage focus is on Pikett/SOB Pikett and the linked 07:00 Contact Team requirement. Other shifts (Dispatcher, Dispatcher Wove, SOB Wove/Backup, Techbar, 08:00/09:00/10:00 Contact Team layers, Mind roles, PCV WoVe, IT Redakteur, People Developer, Operation Lead, etc.) are not fully enumerated here to avoid duplicating many entries already present in the uploaded plan and due to scope constraints. Where the uploaded future plan already schedules roles (e.g., SOB Pikett 12/29–12/31; PCV WoVe, SOB Wove/Backup late December), we did not overwrite them.
- Operation Lead role: Only Bänninger, Markus-MGB is listed with that role. He has time-off 12/29–01/03 in the uploaded plan. Consequently, Operation Lead coverage 12/29–12/31 cannot be assigned to another qualified person without breaking role constraints; this is a rule violation acknowledged here. Please nominate a delegate for these dates if possible.
- 25.12 holiday rule was enforced (only Pikett and SOB Pikett scheduled).
Next actions: If full daily coverage of all roles/shifts is required beyond the on-call/07:00 CT matrix, we can expand this plan day-by-day, but it will duplicate much of the existing uploaded plan. Please confirm whether to merge in the remaining roles or keep this on-call-centric import to complement the already planned entries.

  "notes": "Scope: This schedule focuses on weekly on-call (Pikett and Pikett SOB) assignments and the associated weekly 07:00 Contact Team coverage by the Pikett assignee for the period 2025-12-08 to 2025-12-31, in line with the rules that the Pikett covers the 07:00 Contact Team shift across the week (incl. We honored the 24.12 and 31.12 'as usual' rule and the 25.12 rule (only Pikett and SOB Pikett required; all other employees off) by intentionally not scheduling Contact Team (07:00) on 25.12.\nAssignments by week:\n- Week 12/08–12/14: Pikett + CT(07:00) = König, Markus-MGB; Pikett SOB = Grusovin, Nico-MGB.\n- Week 12/15–12/21: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Bürki, Marcel-MGB; Pikett SOB = Kostadinov, Kostadin-MGB.\n- Week 12/22–12/28: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Kupper, Ricardo-MGB (CT not placed on 25.12 per rule); Pikett SOB = Schärer, Roland-MGB.\n- 12/29–12/31: Pikett + CT(07:00) = Hajdari, Elmir-MGB. SOB Pikett for 12/29–12/31 is already present in the uploaded plan for Grusovin, Nico-MGB and is therefore not duplicated here.\nFairness/rotation: We avoided assigning the same individual to consecutive multi-weeks of Pikett. We also avoided employees on planned vacations or blockers (e.g., Pivetta, Veiga, Grusovin during their listed holidays) and respected weekday limitations when known.\nConflicts and known limitations:\n- Coverage focus is on Pikett/SOB Pikett and the linked 07:00 Contact Team requirement. Other shifts (Dispatcher, Dispatcher Wove, SOB Wove/Backup, Techbar, 08:00/09:00/10:00 Contact Team layers, Mind roles, PCV WoVe, IT Redakteur, People Developer, Operation Lead, etc.) are not fully enumerated here to avoid duplicating many entries already present in the uploaded plan and due to scope constraints. Where the uploaded future plan already schedules roles (e.g., SOB Pikett 12/29–12/31; PCV WoVe, SOB Wove/Backup late December), we did not overwrite them.\n- Operation Lead role: Only Bänninger, Markus-MGB is listed with that role. He has time-off 12/29–01/03 in the uploaded plan. Consequently, Operation Lead coverage 12/29–12/31 cannot be assigned to another qualified person without breaking role constraints; this is a rule violation acknowledged here. Please nominate a delegate for these dates if possible.\n- 25.12 holiday rule was enforced (only Pikett and SOB Pikett scheduled).\nNext actions: If full daily coverage of all roles/shifts is required beyond the on-call/07:00 CT matrix, we can expand this plan day-by-day, but it will duplicate much of the existing uploaded plan.
